Ahead of the 2022 Mark D Ball Men’s Basketball Championship round of 16 slated for Abuja, Novena Heartland Basketball Club of Owerri are leaving nothing to chance for a successful outing. The captain of the side, Chinedu Precious Asogwo, who spoke to Radio Nigeria Sports, rated his Novena Heartland participation in the preliminary phase of Mark D Ball Championship as the toughest competition the club has played in. The 15-year-old Asogwo who stands at 6ft 5inches, however assured that they will work on their strength and stamina, while consolidating on the strong points that aided their qualification to the Round of 16. Having been hired last year, Coach Achu Kingsley Kelechi, said his passion lies with working with relatively unknown players, and it gives him joy to help nurture them to stardom. He commended the CEO of the club, Mr Osita Nwachukwu, for being very supportive and doing his best to prioritise the welfare of the players, while giving them the much needed exposure and career opportunities. “My confidence that we will cope very well in the next phase of the championship, stems from the confidence of my players, who told me when we were to embark on this trip, that competing against elite players and beating the big boys will be fun,” Kelechi said. For Nwachukwu who is the vice president of Igoche Mike-led faction of Nigeria Basketball Federation (NBBF) while reviewing his side performance in the preliminary of the Marl D Ball, which he said was the biggest tournament club have been exposed to, hinted that he may go for a center and shooting guards to help strengthen the club. “I also own Novena Queens, which is the women’s basketball team. Though, both teams in Owerri and Abakiliki we have discovered a good number of talents in the SE, but coming to play in Abuja was a good step up. It gave the guys good exposure.”